age of landscapes weaves together the transmutations underway in the various Cairene geographies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aTravel / Middle East / Egypt.2bisacsh  a2011 Egyptian Revolution.  aCommute.  aEveryday interaction in sociological theory.  aGated communities.  aGentrification.  aMilitarization of urban life.  aModern building as topos.  aNeo-liberalism.  aNostalgia.  aUrban dystopia.1 aAbaza, Mona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614512340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526145123423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526145123/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles